    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER PSO140-61 - DISASSEMBLE - CASE
        AND GEARS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="22">
        <title>CASE AND GEARS</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301412">Figure 12</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301412" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301412" filename="../figg13/G1301412.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 12. Case and Gears Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the output bearing cap and gasket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301413">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301413" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301413" filename="../figg13/G1301413.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Remove Output Bearing Cap and Gasket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft bearing retainers (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301414">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301414" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301414" filename="../figg13/G1301414.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Remove Countershaft Bearing Retainers</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert a bolt into the upper reverse idler shaft and remove the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301415">Figure 15</hotlnk>). Do not lose the lockball in the shaft.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301415" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301415" filename="../figg13/G1301415.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Insert Bolt into Upper Reverse Idler Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Roll the upper reverse idler gear toward the side of the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301416">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301416" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301416" filename="../figg13/G1301416.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Roll Upper Reverse Idler Gear Toward Side of Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Engage the 1st-Reverse collar into reverse gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301417">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301417" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301417" filename="../figg13/G1301417.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Engage 1st-Reverse Collar</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the output shaft bearing. The milled slots facilitate the removal of this bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301418">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301418" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301418" filename="../figg13/G1301418.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Remove Output Shaft Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the mainshaft snap ring and the internally splined thrust washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301419">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301419" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301419" filename="../figg13/G1301419.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Remove Mainshaft Snap Ring and Thrust Washer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the gear bore snap ring and both the externally and internally splined thrust washers
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301420">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301420" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301420" filename="../figg13/G1301420.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Remove Gear Bore Snap Ring and Thrust Washers</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the remaining gear bore snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301421">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301421" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301421" filename="../figg13/G1301421.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. Remove Remaining Gear Bore Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Butt the 1st and reverse gears together (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301422">Figure 22</hotlnk>). Secure both gears with lockwire to provide the necessary
                clearance for removal of the mainshaft assembly.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301422" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301422" filename="../figg13/G1301422.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 22. Butt 1st and Reverse Gears Together</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the clutch housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301423">Figure 23</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301423" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301423" filename="../figg13/G1301423.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 23. Remove Clutch Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the input bearing cap (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301424">Figure 24</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301424" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301424" filename="../figg13/G1301424.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 24. Remove Input Bearing Cap</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the input gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301425">Figure 25</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301425" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301425" filename="../figg13/G1301425.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 25. Remove Input Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a suitable puller to remove the countershaft front bearings (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301426">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301426" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301426" filename="../figg13/G1301426.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 26. Remove Countershaft Front Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the countershafts to the rear as far as possible and install a puller for bearing
                removal (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301427">Figure 27</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301427" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301427" filename="../figg13/G1301427.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 27. Move Countershafts to Rear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To provide adequate clearance for mainshaft removal, move both countershafts forward and
                toward the side of the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301428">Figure 28</hotlnk>). Then lift the mainshaft assembly out of the case.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301428" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301428" filename="../figg13/G1301428.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 28. Move Countershafts Forward</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the upper reverse idler gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301429">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301429" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301429" filename="../figg13/G1301429.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 29. Remove Upper Reverse Idler Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Because of upper idler boss interference, remove the right side countershaft first, then the
                left (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301430">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301430" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301430" filename="../figg13/G1301430.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 30. Remove Right Side Countershaft First, Then Left</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove both the lower reverse idler shaft and gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301431">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301431" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301431" filename="../figg13/G1301431.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 31. Remove Lower Reverse Idler Shaft and Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check both the idler gear and bearings for wear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301432">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301432" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301432" filename="../figg13/G1301432.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 32. Check Idler Gear and Bearings For Wear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <para>
            <title>Gears and Related Parts</title>
        </para>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301433">Figure 33</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301433" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301433" filename="../figg13/G1301433.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 33. Gears and Related Parts Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
